\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 How Tool/Skill Triggering Works\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 There are 
\f1\b three layers
\f2\b0  of triggering, from most automatic to most manual:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 1. Fully Automatic (Default Behavior)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 AGENTS.md instructs Claude to 
\f1\b take initiative without asking
\f2\b0 . When you start a new session and describe your task, Claude should:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Read 
\f3\fs26 registry.json
\f2\fs24  automatically\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Classify your task against the 
\f1\b Auto-Activation Map
\f2\b0  (16 intent patterns)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Clone/install the matching tools immediately\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Report what was activated and why\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Example:
\f2\b0  You say "I have a PRD, build this app" \uc0\u8594  Claude auto-activates 
\f3\fs26 autonomous-agent-system
\f2\fs24  + 
\f3\fs26 token-efficiency
\f2\fs24  + 
\f3\fs26 claude-mem
\f2\fs24  + 
\f3\fs26 recall-stack
\f2\fs24  + 
\f3\fs26 everything-claude-code
\f2\fs24  without you needing to specify anything.\
The matching works through:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 activation_triggers
\f2\b0\fs24  in registry.json \'97 keyword arrays like 
\f3\fs26 ["PRD", "product requirements", "build from spec"]
\f2\fs24 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 anti_triggers
\f2\b0\fs24  \'97 keywords that prevent false matches (e.g., 
\f3\fs26 ["quick fix", "one-liner"]
\f2\fs24  prevents heavy tools on simple tasks)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 priority
\f2\b0\fs24  values \'97 higher priority tools get activated first when multiple match\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Tool combinations
\f2\b0  \'97 predefined stacks like 
\f3\fs26 prd-full-build
\f2\fs24  that bundle the right tools together\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 2. Contextual Matching (Intelligent Selection)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 For the 256 agent-skills-mega skills and 8 creator skills, Claude searches the index files to find the best match. For example:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 You say "write me a reel script" \uc0\u8594  Claude reads 
\f3\fs26 skills_index.json
\f2\fs24 , finds 
\f3\fs26 killer-scripter.skill
\f2\fs24  has triggers 
\f3\fs26 ["write a script", "write a reel"]
\f2\fs24 , loads it automatically\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 You say "pentest this API" \uc0\u8594  Claude searches the 256-skill index, finds the penetration testing skill, reads it from 
\f3\fs26 repos/agent-skills-mega/
\f2\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 3. Manual Override (When You Want Control)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 You can always be explicit:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 toolbelt activate [id]
\f2\b0\fs24  \'97 force-activate a specific tool\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 toolbelt scan
\f2\b0\fs24  \'97 ask Claude to analyze your current task and recommend tools\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 toolbelt status
\f2\b0\fs24  \'97 see what's available and what's already cloned\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls14\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Or just name it: "use the paul-framework for this" or "load the content-repurposer skill"\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 The Reality Check\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 The automatic triggering depends on one critical prerequisite: 
\f1\b Claude must read AGENTS.md at session start.
\f2\b0  This happens because:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Your global 
\f3\fs26 ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md
\f2\fs24  contains the CLAUDE HQ activation protocol\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls16\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It instructs Claude to fetch and follow AGENTS.md for any major project\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls17\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The trigger words "activate HQ", "claude hq", or providing a PRD all kick it off\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 For best results:
\f2\b0  At the start of any serious project session, either say "activate HQ" or just describe your task naturally \'97 the system is designed to pattern-match your intent and auto-activate the right stack. You should rarely need to manually specify tools unless you want something very specific that doesn't match the obvious keywords.\
}